"The husband acts the part called the understanding and the wife acts the part called the will." - Swedenborg

Mirrors how in Hinduism the "power" of a deity is called his bride, Shiva is un-acting while Shakti acts, etc. Julius Evola explains it well in "The Yoga of Power" book.

"From this it is that in the word "youth" or "man" means in the spiritual sense the understanding of truth, and "virgin" or "woman" affection for good;"

Again in this sense "man" is "vir", an eminent person with capacity for spiritual perception (opposed to earth-bound "pashu").
Pretty sure Evola never mentioned Swedenborg even though the two overlap very obviously

"This conjunction is actual conjunction, for the will of the wife enters into the understanding of the husband, and the understanding of the husband into the will of the wife, and this especially when they look into one another's faces;"

All of Swedenborg seems to focus on faces

"With the Man the Understanding predominates, and with the Woman the Will predominates. Yet in heavenly marriages there is no predominance; for the will of the wife is also the husband's will, and the understanding of the husband is also the wife's understanding." - E. Swedenborg

The bottom line is that any profound spiritual insight will be contained in a chaotic form, mixed with falsehood, and could be found in the writings of the Church, the Scriptures, the Saints, etc. in a less dangerous form. Yet one appreciates Swedenborg's "mechanic" intelligence.

Because I posted a few Swedenborg excerpts this week, I will also share Rene Guenon's warning that one "cannot take too many precautions" if one wishes to extract real value from his/other such spiritualist writers' texts. Anything of "genuine interest" is still not in pure form.
